description.narrative:
The TMT Strengthening Dairy Cooperative's Extension and Training Services is a one year capacity building program in a partnership between NL based KIT and Agriterra and the Kenyan union of dairy cooperative BAMSCOS in Baringo, Kenya. Since early 2017 BAMSCOS is undertaking systematic efforts to build its own extension services with technical support from Agriterra and this TMT was initiated as a review and capacity building trajectory. It benefits from insights generated during a recent study by Agriterra and KIT on Agribusiness-based Advisory Services (ABAS).

The main activities of this projects are:

· A strategic review and capacity building workshops with management and leaders of BAMSCOS and its member cooperatives on the organization and functioning of the extension service;

· An intensive training workshop for extension staff and farmer leaders on extension communication approaches, methods and tools;

· A dairy technical training for extension staff and farmer leaders;

· A season long coaching of field extension staff and farmer leaders in running a focused extension program using improved insights and skills gained during the training workshops;

· Two review and refresher workshops, one with leaders and management of BAMSCOS followed by one with extension staff and farmer leaders.

At the end of the trajectory KIT and Agriterra will work with BAMSCOS to produce and E-publishing a 4 page Learning Brief documenting main experiences and lessons learnt under this project.
